questions.question: What is ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage?
questions.answer: ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage is an extension node for ComfyUI that allows users to select a resolution from pre-defined json files and output a Latent Image.

questions.question: How does ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage retrieve a list of resolutions?
questions.answer: The node retrieves a list of resolutions from a json file saved in a specific format and displays them in a dropdown list on the node's interface.

questions.question: Can I select a resolution manually in ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage?
questions.answer: No, you cannot select a resolution manually. You must choose from the pre-defined resolutions in the dropdown list provided by the node.

questions.question: What is the aspect ratio displayed in the dropdown list?
questions.answer: The aspect ratio displayed in the dropdown list is calculated as `width / height` of the selected resolution.

questions.question: Does ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage come with pre-defined resolution sets?
questions.answer: Yes, the [sdxl_resolution_set.json](sdxl_resolution_set.json) file is provided with a set of resolutions considered optimal for training in SDXL.

questions.question: How can I load a custom resolution file?
questions.answer: During node initialization, you can load a .json file with custom resolution settings. A sample resolution set for SD1.5 is provided in [sd_resolution_set.json](sd_resolution_set.json).

questions.question: How do I install ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage?
questions.answer: To install, navigate to the 'custom_nodes' folder where ComfyUI is installed, then use 'git clone' to clone the [ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage](https://github.com/shingo1228/ComfyUI-SDXL-EmptyLatentImage) repository as per the instructions.
